Ordering food from this establishment, since the  covid pandemic is a hit or miss. The first time I ordered the food was tasty. The second time I ordered. The food was horrible! I ordered BBQ ribs and shrimp fried rice. Ribs were  old and dried out tough bones. And, the rice was not fresh. This was the same exact order I ordered the first time. I will not be returning to this restaurant! Generally when I visit  this restaurant, the food is great . More recently I've noticed that the quality of the food on the lunch menu has changed . I received food that was Luke warm and sometimes the rice side was completely cold. The first incident that occurred was a bit less offensive than the second. I decided to dine in one day with a friend, we paid for our food and we forgot to leave a tip because we were rushing to a movie. The lady at the front door stopped us before we left and demanded that we explain why we didn't leave a tip. She pushed the issue and insisted that we pay our waiter their tip, which we would have done if we had not forgot and we did but we left the restaurant feeling quite uncomfortable. The next incident was more of a silent offense when I visited the restaurant with a male friend of mine from Spain. We didn't feel welcome in the restaurant and we received rude stares from the staff , who took the liberty of bringing our check way before we asked for it. While eating we felt extremely uncomfortable and my lunch companion vowed never to return to this restaurant again because we felt like we were on display. The last straw occurred a few months later when  I  had a problem with a young girl who worked behind the register. I ordered food from the lunch menu and I was told that there was a minimum of ten dollars for cards . I left and returned after getting money from the bank and got back on line . The lady in front of me was picking up food also . Her food , like mine cost less than $10.00. However she being older than me , as well as a white woman while I'm am not, was allowed to use her card without any difficulties, and was treated respectfully . So I decided I would not spend my money at a restaurant that does not treat their customers equally. This whole situation has left a bad taste in my mouth about the restaurant . I have not returned to this restaurant  since.

So far so good. Not a lot of people in here but the delivery service is non stop. We ordered steamed beef dumplings, general tso and  I ordered the scallop house special. Mine was kind of kind general tso but with scallops. It was good. The actual general tso was a tad salty for me the person who ordered it preferred my dish. We all liked the dumplings. The people are great. Attentive and were nice to a "baby". They gave extra napkins and said, "you have baby". Haha The atmosphere is nice. The prices are a tad more than usual dinky Chinese food stores. There's a reason. It's better than dinky stores. Love the tea pot. Good to drink warm things after a meal.  No one takes a shot of the restroom. I guess I might be a first LOL not the best place I've been to but it's also not the worst.  Edit: Been here few times after review. It's a cozy place. We'll probably keep coming. No issues the 4 times we've been here.

I just placed my last order from Lichee Nut. We started ordering here a few years back. The food was always good and hot, and delivery was fast. Then we got a delivery man who yelled at me. Then they started making mistakes. My order tonight was sesame noodles for my wife, and dumplings and subgum noodle soup for me. 2/3 dishes are correct. I was really in the mood for soup, but alas my subgum has no broth. Plenty of other options in the neighborhood. I'm moving on. It's been real.

I  went with my daughter for lunch to Lychee Nut restaurant on Montague in downtown Brooklyn , and my experience was horrible because when I paid our meal , and  was getting ready to tip the individual who was serving me he had left and 2 other employees in the restaurant blocked me from leaving if I didn't tip them or they were threatening to call the police on me if  I refuse to tip them, and I am a disable individual on crutches.  I don't Recommend this restaurant to  to my worst enemy even Satan.

The food isn't that special and the prices are exorbitant. The food from the regular and less expensive Chinese restaurants taste way better, plus the servers don't ask for tip, like my experience at this restaurant shown. After I wrote the tip amount the server came back to me and asked for more because it wasn't within the required 15% that is supposedly included. Then they throw a fit about me not tipping them. I've worked in the service industry and I have never asked for tip from anyone. You don't harass someone and then throw temper tantrums about not receiving the "appropriate" 15% gratuituty. Closing, I only gave $2 because the service wasn't that great to begin with.

This isn't your typical hope in the wall,  foggy glassed chinese restaurant. You can eat in as well as easy out.  Very comfy atmosphere with very nice service. I got the vegetarian chicken in hot pepper sauce.  While the chicken was bland  (compared to other vegetarian chicken I've had)  it was still enjoyable.  It was nice to know that there was a nice, clean Chinese place with plenty of vegan options in the neighborhood.
Typical neighborhood Chinese food. Don't look for any special food it service, but it gets the job done.

If you have any decency and self pride i would advise you not step inside this classless racist establishment. My mother and i decided to have a quick evening meal there this summer while vacationing in NY,after receiving our meal (which was culinary mediocracy  at  best) if i must say so,we asked for the waiter to bring our check. Upon the waiter returning with our check we left a payment for what was owed and began to leave as we didn't find it necessary to leave a tip for the waiters average service,,which consisted of him just simply placing an order and bringing us our order with not one touch of customer personalization or friendliness. As we began to leave he followed us to the door asking" where his tip was",,my mother explained that we were not gonna be able to tip today,he than stormed away and grabbed his manager who then came out and decided to scold and chastise us in front of a room filled with customers  on the policy of tip-giving and how his employess dont make much. After going on for what seemed to be like10 minutes i explained what "gratuity" was and how it is  optional and also how him scolding us in front of people about not leaving a tip was not only disrespectful but totally unprofessional,,,he then told us to shut up and get out and while we were speaking he had a young lady behind the counter turn up the music volume on full blast to drown us out all while others were still dining. Ive never had such a discusting experience in my life,do yourself a favor and skip this joint and spend your money with an establishment that carries themselves with a little more dignity and pride

the stuff is delicious and the price is reasonable

Eh very disappointed... The bad...My shrimp and broccoli was made with baby shrimp!!!! Who makes shrimp and broccoli with baby shrimp!!!!! I guess since baby shrimp are already cooked they barely cooked my broccoli, crisp OK damn near raw, something different. The spring roll wasnt fully cooked inside And mushy on the outside, and there was a shrimp inside my spring roll. The wonton soup was flavorless and the crispy noodles were maybe fried in not yet hot grease, since you could still see and taste all the oil.  The good,The flavor was 3*. The brown rice is higher quality than most. My friend said her chicken broccoli had good flavor as well.... So maybe just stay away from the appetizers.

I order chicken wings with fried rice, I couldn't eat it the smell was like when the meat is spoil. The nasty waitress who seem to hate his job told me that he would give me fried rice and shrimp broccoli. Okay given the fact that I'm pregnant and I wanted to eat Chinese I agree. He brought me the food and the shrimps smell worse than the chicken wing that a couple seating on a table behind me smell it and walked out, at that point I told the guy I don't want it give me the bill, by saying give me the bill I was expecting to pay for the soda that I did consume. I get a $15.50 bill for the chicken wings and for the shrimps I asked the guy why was he charging me for something I didn't consume and he say acting like he is mentally in capacited that he is doing he is job. If you want to waste to your lunch hour and your money THIS IS THE BEST PLACE TO COME!

Still the food is good, service is nice easy and fast, menu is easy to read. Seating can be a little awkward, small restaurant with a few even smaller tables. So you risk the chance of being seated at a table with a complete stranger, especially if you come alone. But my waiter chased me out the door asking about a tip, so... Three stars it is
